        <h1>Motivation</h1>
            <h3>How does life look through the 'pleasure, passion and purpose' lens?</h3>
              <p>
                What i took from this chapter is that fleeting pleasures will not keep you happy.You have to keep chasing them and they will not last long, the flow i am not sure about, the higher purpose happiness is interesting. I think it is like when you decode on a goal. A goal that you are really passionate about, it might be far off in the future but your are so excited about it that it fules your motiviation. When I first enrolled in university, i didnt know what i wanted to do so i took some random papers to see what i liked, one of those papers was in "dynamtic websites with PHP and HTML". When i started this paper i found i really enjoyed it. i decided that was the way to go and one day i would be a web developer and could enjoy my work, that fuled me to work on my assignments ect but i started not caring about any other papers i had signed up for i lost all interest because i had this goal in mind and i only wnted to work on the things that would get me there.<br>
I think this is what is meant by higher purpose, im not sure.... 
              </p>
